# Gacha Build Planner — Core Rules

## Project context

Next.js 14 app for Genshin Impact and Honkai: Star Rail build planning. Read `AGENTS.md` for architecture and directory layout.

## Must follow

- Use `@/` path alias for imports; respect perfectionist import sort order.
- Keep `calculation/` free of React — pure functions only.
- Game-specific logic goes in `types/genshin/` or `types/starrail/` and matching `DataProvider`; share via `types/` interfaces (`IBuild`, `IDataContext`, etc.).
- Persist user data through `StorageContext` / IndexedDB, not ad-hoc localStorage.
- Validate imported data with existing AJV schemas in `dataimport/`.
- Run `npm run lint` after substantive TS/TSX changes; run `npm test` when touching `calculation/` or `__tests__/`.

## Avoid

- Duplicating game logic in components — use `IDataContext` and `IBuild` methods.
- Broad refactors or unrelated cleanup in focused tasks.
- Committing `.env` files or secrets.
